newsitem.title: UK: UK physical grains quiet and unchanged.
newsitem.headline: UK physical grains quiet and unchanged.

text.p: UK physical grains were quiet and unchanged on Friday as the pre-Christmas doldrums took hold of the market.
Traders on the fob market report no activity and virtually no markets.
"Some of the French co-operatives have closed already and will remain shut until January 6. When the biggest European producers market dies, so does ours," said a trader.
Delivered trade was also slow with traded levels little changed from Thursday.
Feed wheat in the middle of the country was trading at 96 stg for January while in the Avon range 99.50 stg was paid.
Milling wheat 11 percent protein in the Tilbury area fetched 115 stg for January and 119.50 in Liverpool.
Feed barley on the south coast traded at 100 stg for January.
